{"name":"Donair Power Bowl","slug":"donair-power-bowl","description":"<p>Power Bowls are perfect for meal prep. This one is a great way to use up leftover <a data-item-id=\"382f37e8-7e49-4ed4-9acd-e0df1fb9dae3\" href=\"\">Donair</a> and then simply assemble with a cooked grain, sliced veggies, and a dressing! You’ll have enough bowls for lunches for the work week.</p>","ingredients":[{"name":"Roasted Garlic Aioli","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> cup prepared","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Roasted Garlic Aioli Mix","quantity":"1 tbsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"light mayonnaise","quantity":"1 cup","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"lemon juice","quantity":"1 tsp","additionalInstruction":"optional"},{"name":"hot water","quantity":"1 <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> tbsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"sugar","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>4</sub> tsp","additionalInstruction":"optional"},{"name":"large tomatoes","quantity":"3","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"English cucumbers","quantity":"2","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"small red onion","quantity":"1","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"cooked quinoa","quantity":"5 cups","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Donair","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> recipe prepared","additionalInstruction":"sliced"},{"name":"Donair Seasoning","quantity":"1 pkg","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"lean ground beef","quantity":"2 lbs (900 g)","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"water","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>4</sub> cup ","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"whole-wheat pitas","quantity":"10 ","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"East Coast Donair Sauce or Dillicious Tzatziki","quantity":"1 cup","additionalInstruction":"optional"},{"name":"mayonnaise","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> cup ","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"milk","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>4</sub> cup","additionalInstruction":"your choice"},{"name":"sugar","quantity":"2 tbsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"white vinegar","quantity":"2 tsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Roasted Garlic Aioli Mix","quantity":"1 <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> tsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"2% plain Greek yogurt","quantity":"1 cup","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Lemon Dilly Dip Mix","quantity":"1 tbsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"English cucumber","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub>","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Sea Salt","quantity":null,"additionalInstruction":"to taste"},{"name":"Black Pepper","quantity":null,"additionalInstruction":"to taste"},{"name":"tomatoes","quantity":"2","additionalInstruction":"sliced"},{"name":"English cucumber","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub>","additionalInstruction":"sliced"},{"name":"red onion","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub>","additionalInstruction":"thinly sliced"},{"name":"head romaine or leafy green lettuce","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> ","additionalInstruction":null}],"totalTime":"20 min","servings":"5 servings","preparation":"<ol>\n  <li>For dressing, in a small bowl, whisk together aioli, hot water, and sugar, if using. Set aside.</li>\n  <li>Chop tomatoes. Using <a data-item-id=\"ab3c5569-ead1-4e8c-b4d4-6506a11c8b1f\" href=\"\">Y Peeler</a>, peel cucumbers lengthwise into ribbons. Cut onion in half; thinly slice.</li>\n  <li>Divide quinoa, veggies, and donair between five bowls. Drizzle with dressing and sprinkle with topper, if desired.</li>\n</ol>","tags":[{"slug":"sugar_conscious","name":"Sugar Conscious"},{"slug":"one_dish","name":"One Dish"},{"slug":"dinner","name":"Dinner"},{"slug":"lunch","name":"Lunch"},{"slug":"no_cook","name":"No-Cook"},{"slug":"gluten_free_e8446d0","name":"Gluten-free"},{"slug":"high_protein","name":"High Protein"},{"slug":"dairy_free","name":"Dairy-free"},{"slug":"beef","name":"Beef"}],"nutritionalInformation":{"servingSize":"","calories":510,"fat":21,"saturatedFat":5,"transFat":0.3,"cholesterol":55,"sodium":570,"carbohydrate":53,"fiber":9,"sugars":7,"protein":29},"tips":"<p>Prepare a large batch of quinoa in the <a data-item-id=\"bd092c36-a4ba-5b73-9abc-fa95c0102e9a\" href=\"\">Multipurpose Steamer</a>. Combine 2 cups uncooked quinoa with 4 cups water or broth. Microwave on high, uncovered, 20–22 min, stirring halfway through. Quinoa should be tender. Set aside to cool. Gently fluff with a fork before serving. This recipe yields about 5 cups quinoa (perfect for this power bowl recipe!).</p>\n<p>Tomatoes are so delicious at this time of year. Switch it up and try cherry tomatoes, which come in a variety of shapes and colours; simply slice in half and add to your bowls.</p>","perfectlyBalanceYourPlate":"<p>This is a perfectly balanced plate.</p>"}